  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/06b38cae31fcc9a4db19b6ac10e053f708135b9c" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:2.574ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \mathbf {p} _{k}}"></span> are conjugated and again that the residuals are orthogonal. This gives the <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \beta }">
