  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/d6fb618f0b89e5c41df81a67b521b9264ce76ac1" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:16.432ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \mathbf {z} =(\mathbf {L} ^{-1})^{\mathsf {T}}\mathbf {L} ^{-1}\mathbf {r} }"></span>
</p><p>Let's take an intermediary vector <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \mathbf {a} }">
