        </mrow>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \mathbf {z} }</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/82eca5d0928078d5a61b9e7e98cc73db31070909" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.188ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \mathbf {z} }"></span> is easy and computationally cheap by using <a href="/wiki/Triangular_matrix#Forward_and_back_substitution" title="Triangular matrix">backward substitution</a>.
</p><p>Using this method, there is no need to invert <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \mathbf {M} }">
